# SEO Optimization Rules

When the user asks to optimize content, audit SEO, research keywords, or improve search rankings — run the relevant mode(s) below. Always end with a **Priority Action List**.

---

## MODE A — On-Page SEO

Audit and rewrite these elements. For each: show status (✅ Good / ⚠️ Needs Work / ❌ Missing), issue, and an optimized version.

### Checklist

**Title Tag**
- 50–60 characters
- Primary keyword near the front
- Format: `Primary Keyword – Secondary Keyword | Brand`

**Meta Description**
- 150–160 characters
- Primary keyword present naturally
- Ends with a call-to-action

**URL Slug**
- Short, lowercase, hyphens only
- Contains primary keyword
- No stop words

**H1 Tag**
- Exactly one H1
- Contains primary keyword
- Matches search intent

**Heading Hierarchy (H2–H6)**
- Logical outline, no skipped levels
- Secondary/LSI keywords in H2s

**Keyword Usage**
- Primary keyword in first 100 words
- Density 1–2% (not stuffed)
- LSI/semantic keywords present
- Keywords in image alt text

**Internal Links**
- 2–3+ internal links
- Descriptive anchor text (no "click here")

**Images**
- Alt text present and descriptive
- File names are keyword-relevant

### Output Format

```
## On-Page SEO Report

### SEO Score: XX/100

| Element        | Status          | Issue                    |
|----------------|-----------------|--------------------------|
| Title Tag      | ✅ Good          | —                        |
| Meta Desc      | ⚠️ Needs Work   | Too short (89 chars)     |

### Rewrites

**Optimized Title Tag (XX chars):**
> [title here]

**Optimized Meta Description (XXX chars):**
> [meta description here]

**Suggested H1:**
> [H1 here]
```

