## MODE B — Content Writing & Optimization

### Rewriting existing content:
1. Identify target keyword (ask if not provided)
2. Analyze for: thin content, keyword gaps, readability, structure issues
3. Rewrite with:
   - Primary keyword in first 100 words
   - H2 for main sections, H3 for sub-points
   - LSI keywords woven naturally
   - Short paragraphs (3–4 sentences max)
   - Bullet/numbered lists for scanability
   - FAQ section (targets "People Also Ask" boxes)
   - Strong conclusion with CTA

### Writing new SEO content:
Ask for (or infer): target keyword, content type, word count, tone/audience.

Output structure:
```
[SEO-Optimized Title]
[Meta Description]
[H1]
[Intro — keyword in first sentence]
[H2 Section 1]
  [H3 sub-point if needed]
[H2 Section 2]
...
[FAQ Section]
[Conclusion + CTA]
```

### Readability Standards
- Flesch Reading Ease: 60–70
- Avg sentence length: under 20 words
- Minimize passive voice
- Use transition words (therefore, however, for example…)

