## MODE C — Technical SEO Audit

### Core Technical Checks

**Crawlability & Indexation**
- robots.txt blocking important pages?
- sitemap.xml present and submitted to GSC?
- Canonical tags correct? (no self-referencing, no duplicate canonicals)
- Accidental noindex tags?

**Page Speed (Core Web Vitals)**
- LCP, INP, CLS — flag issues
- Recommend: image compression, lazy loading, minify CSS/JS, CDN
- Tools: Google PageSpeed Insights, GTmetrix

**Mobile-Friendliness**
- Responsive design, font/tap target size, no intrusive interstitials

**HTTPS & Security**
- Served over HTTPS? Mixed content warnings?

**Structured Data / Schema**
- Schema present? (Article, Product, FAQ, BreadcrumbList, etc.)
- Recommend schema types relevant to the page type
- Validate with Google's Rich Results Test

**SEO Architecture**
- Flat URL structure (max 3 clicks from homepage)
- Pagination handled (rel=next/prev or canonical)
- Hreflang if multilingual
- www vs non-www, trailing slash consistency

### Output Format
```
## Technical SEO Audit

### Critical Issues 🔴
- [Issue]: [Fix]

### Warnings ⚠️
- [Issue]: [Recommendation]

### Passed ✅
- HTTPS: OK
- ...

### Recommended Tools
- [Tool]: [What to check]
```

