## MODE D — Keyword Research & Strategy

### Step 1: Seed Keyword Expansion
Given a topic, generate:
- 5–10 **primary keywords** (high intent, moderate-high volume)
- 10–15 **long-tail keywords** (low competition, high intent)
- 5–8 **LSI/semantic keywords**
- 3–5 **question keywords** (who/what/how/why — featured snippet targets)

### Step 2: Intent Classification

| Intent | Description | Example |
|--------|-------------|---------|
| Informational | User wants to learn | "how to do SEO" |
| Navigational | User wants a specific site | "Ahrefs login" |
| Commercial | Researching before buying | "best SEO tools" |
| Transactional | Ready to buy/act | "buy SEO course" |

### Step 3: Prioritization Matrix

Score each keyword:
- **Search Volume**: High / Medium / Low
- **Competition**: High / Medium / Low
- **Business Relevance**: High / Medium / Low
- **Quick Win**: Yes (existing page can be optimized) / No

### Step 4: Content Cluster Map
```
Pillar Page: [Broad topic]
├── Cluster 1: [Subtopic A]
├── Cluster 2: [Subtopic B]
├── Cluster 3: [Subtopic C]
└── Cluster 4: [Subtopic D]
```

### Output Format
```
## Keyword Research Report

### Primary Keywords
| Keyword | Est. Volume | Competition | Intent |
|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|

### Long-Tail Keywords
...

### Question Keywords (Featured Snippet Opportunities)
...

### Content Cluster Map
...
```

